1. Installed Node.js on Windows.
2. Opened VS Code.
3. Opened the alx-intermediate-frontend folder.
4. Opened the VS Code terminal.
5. Created the folder 0x03-sass_scss.
6. Installed Sass with the command: npm install sass -v 3.7.4
7. Created the file 0-installation-script.

8. Added the command npm install sass -v 3.7.4 to the file 0-installation-script.
9. Made the file executable with the command: chmod +x 0-installation-script.
10. Verified the installation script by running: ./0-installation-script
#!/bin/bash
npm install sass -v 3.7.4
